<HEADLINE>  Arafat to Israelis: 'Elect Peace' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JERUSALEM (AP) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat had a simple  
message today for Israelis heading to the polls: ``Elect peace.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Short in words, the message was long in meaning: a carefully  
couched appeal to vote for Labor's moderate candidate, Ehud Barak. 
</P>
<P>
	In public statements, Palestinian leaders have tried to remain  
neutral in Israel's race for the premiership. But behind the 
