<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> RealNetworks in Music, Video Deals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- RealNetworks Inc. and Snap.com today announced a  
pair of deals that will help Internet users find music and video on 
the Web. 
</P>
<P>
	RealNetworks said it will incorporate a search feature into its  
RealPlayer G2 software using Snap.com technology as the search 
engine, the companies said in a joint statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Snap.com, the San Francisco-based Internet portal from NBC and  
CNET, becomes the exclusive search feature on RealPlayer G2, 
allowing users to search directly for RealAudio and RealVideo files 
on the Web. 
</P>
<P>
	There are more than 60 million registered users of RealPlayer,  
free software that enables people to listen to music and watch 
video through the Internet, the Seattle-based RealNetworks said. 
</P>
<P>
	In a second deal, Snap.com said it will create a portal site for  
users with fast Internet connections. The portal will use 
programming from RealGuide, a guide produced by RealNetworks, 
providing listings of audio and video from more than 1,700 radio 
and television stations on the Web. 
</P>
<P>
	The RealGuide content will also be available in the original  
Snap.com site and RealNetworks said it will use Snap.com search 
technology on its other Web sites, including Film.com and 
MusicNet.com. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
