<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Seahawks Allowed To Use UW Stadium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- The University of Washington reached an agreement  
Monday with the Seattle Seahawks that will allow the NFL team to 
use Husky Stadium for home games in 2000 and 2001. 
</P>
<P>
	The university's Board of Regents must approve the agreement at  
its May 21 meeting. The Seattle City Council also must approve the 
Seahawks' use of the stadium because of the effect on traffic. 
</P>
<P>
	The Seahawks now play in the Kingdome. They need the alternate  
location because the Kingdome is being demolished to make way for a 
new football-soccer stadium at the Kingdome site. 
</P>
<P>
	Under the agreement, the Seahawks agree to pay the university  
$305,000 per game in rent. The Seahawks expect to play 10 NFL games 
at Husky Stadium each season, eight in the regular season and two 
exhibitions. 
</P>
<P>
	To address concerns of stadium neighbors, the Seahawks also have  
agreed not to sell alcohol in the stadium and not to schedule home 
games on weekdays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
