<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Limited's Earnings, Sales Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- The Limited Inc. said its first-quarter  
earnings rose nearly 30 percent as results improved at several of 
its clothing store chains. 
</P>
<P>
	The nation's largest specialty apparel retailer reported Monday  
its net income, which excludes one-time items, was $33.5 million, 
or 14 cents per share, in the quarter ended May 1, up from $25.8 
million, or 9 cents per share, in the same period last year. 
</P>
<P>
	The results met the expectations of analysts surveyed by First  
Call Corp. 
</P>
<P>
	One-time items included the divestiture of the Abercrombie &AMP;  
Fitch chain last year. When one-time items are factored in, 
Limited's earnings fell nearly 58 percent from $79.4 million, or 28 
cents per share, a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales rose 4.8 percent to $2.1 billion from nearly $2.01  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Limited, which has been restructuring its struggling businesses  
over the past few years, reported an improved performance at 
several chains including Express, Lerner New York, Lane Bryant, 
Limited Too and Intimate Brands. 
</P>
<P>
	But Jeffrey Stein, an analyst with McDonald Investments Inc. of  
Cleveland, said the company is still struggling in the highly 
competitive retail business. 
</P>
<P>
	``They still have a ways to go yet,'' Stein said today. ``They  
still continue to lose money in their women's businesses. It takes 
more than two seasons to convince me that the business is turning 
around, but there is progress.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Stein said the flagship Limited chain and Structure, which sells  
men's clothes, are struggling. 
</P>
<P>
	The Limited announced plans recently to spin off its Limited Too  
girls clothing chain this summer and sell its majority interest in 
its Galyan's Trading Co. sporting goods stores. 
</P>
<P>
	The Limited operates about 3,600 stores, including the Express,  
Lerner New York, Lane Bryant and Limited Stores chains. The company 
also owns about 84 percent of Intimate Brands Inc., which operates 
more than 1,800 stores through Victoria's Secret and Bath &AMP; Body 
Works. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
