<HEADLINE> Sen. Dole May Make Pledge to McCain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Former Sen. Bob Dole says he's not sure his wife  
will seek the Republican presidential nomination. He's even 
considering contributing to the campaign of one of her competitors, 
Sen. John McCain. 
</P>
<P>
	``McCain's my friend. And he's not raising the money that (Texas  
Gov.) George Bush is. I think we need to keep good people in the 
race,'' Dole said in an interview in today's New York Times. ``So 
I've thought about ways to help McCain in particular.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But before writing out the check, the former senator added, ``I  
think I'd check with Elizabeth first.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McCain, an Arizonan, is an announced candidate for the GOP  
nomination in 2000. Bush and Mrs. Dole are exploring whether to 
formally enter the race. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm sort of leaning that she'll do it,'' said Dole, who ran  
three times for the presidency. ``If there's no response out there, 
or if it looks impossible, this is not her whole life. If she can't 
raise the money, obviously it's pretty hard to be a candidate.'' 
</P>
