Belmont. 
</P>
<P>
	Charismatic, trained by D. Wayne Lukas, was accompanied by  
stablemate Cat Thief on the 1 1/2-hour flight from Baltimore to 
Louisville. 
</P>
<P>
	``He shipped very well,'' Lukas said. ``It's an easy trip.''  
</P>
<P>
	Charismatic, a son of Summer Squall owned by Robert and Beverly  
Lewis, was bathed and then walked in the shedrow before being taken 
out to graze in a grassy area alongside Churchill's barns. 
</P>
<P>
	Charismatic has won his last three races, starting with the  
Lexington Stakes at Keeneland two weeks before the Derby. 
</P>
<P>
	``He just continues to amaze me,'' Lukas said. ``He was out on  
the lawn yesterday, grazing at Pimlico, and he didn't look any 
different than he did Friday when we had him out there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Lukas said Charismatic's tentative training schedule before the  
Belmont Stakes probably will include two workouts at Churchill 
Downs before being shipped to Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Lukas said Overbrook Farm's Cat Thief, third in the Derby, is  
off the Triple Crown trail after engaging in a withering speed duel 
in the Preakness and will skip the Belmont Stakes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
