<HEADLINE> 'The Mummy' Leads Box Office / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- As Hollywood braced for the ``Star Wars''  
invasion, ``The Mummy'' and two other holdovers led the North 
American box office, while newcomers ``Black Mask'' and ``A 
Midsummer Night's Dream'' did respectable business, final numbers 
showed Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Mummy'' collected $24.9 million to boost its total to  
$80.6 million, exceeding industry expectations for the adventure 
tale starring Brendan Fraser. It beat ``Entrapment,'' which had 
$9.1 million for second, and ``The Matrix,'' with $4.5 million for 
third. 
</P>
<P>
	Studios released no major films over the weekend, making room  
for Wednesday's opening of ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom 
Menace.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But two new films in moderately wide release did moderately  
well. The martial arts movie ``Black Mask'' had $4.4 million for 
fourth and ``William Shakespeare's A Midsummer Night's Dream'' 
collected $4.3 million for fifth. 
</P>
