<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Drops 152.06 on Fed Worries / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks fell sharply today, sending the Dow Jones  
industrial average falling more than 150 points, as investors 
traded cautiously in advance of Tuesday's Federal Reserve meeting. 
</P>
<P>
	At noon on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
down 152.06 at 10,761.26. Broader stock indicators were also lower. 
</P>
<P>
	Today's losses extended Friday's broad selloff, when the Dow  
fell 193.87 to 10,913.32. Investors sold stocks and bonds alike 
after a steeper-than-expected increase in the consumer price index 
fed worries that the booming economy might finally fall prey to 
inflation. 
</P>
<P>
	The report prompted speculation that the Fed will at least  
consider an interest rate hike when its Open Market Committee meets 
Tuesday. In the meantime, many traders appeared willing to wait on 
the sidelines, as volume was well behind Friday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	``The market is paying respects to the FOMC today,'' said Alfred  
E. Goldman, chief market strategist at A.G. Edwards &AMP; Sons Inc. in 
St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
	The Fed tightens rates when central bankers believe the economy  
is growing too fast. Higher interest rates raise corporate 
borrowing rates, which can often hurt profits. 
</P>
<P>
	Big mergers influenced trading in individual stocks today. As  
former Baby Bell U S West and telecommunications company Global 
Crossing announced they would merge, the stocks of both companies 
fell. Global Crossing was down 2 7/8 at 58 1/2 on Nasdaq, while U S West 
slipped 4 1/2 to 57 3/4 on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	Wyman Gordon was the biggest percentage gainer on the Big Board,  
rising 5 7/16 to 18 11/16, after Precision Castparts Corp. agreed 
to acquire it for about $721 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was down 16.15 at 1,321.65, and  
the Nasdaq composite index was off 32.28 at 2,495.58. 
</P>
<P>
	Declining issues outnumbered advancers by an 11-to-4 margin on  
the NYSE, where volume came to 288.8 million shares. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was down 7.53 at 630.92, and the  
American Stock Exchange composite index was down 9.69 at 779.12. 

</P>
</TEXT>
