<HEADLINE> Rojas Rejoins Expos in Minors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MONTREAL (AP) -- The Montreal Expos signed their former closer  
Mel Rojas, who has struggled since leaving the team, to a minor 
league contract on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Rojas is joining Montreal's Class A team in Jupiter, Fla. He is  
expected to join the major league team after a few outings in 
Jupiter. 
</P>
<P>
	``We didn't sign him to keep him in the minors,'' said manager  
Felipe Alou, who wanted Rojas back. ``We want him here. 
</P>
<P>
	``If he pitches well, he can help us.''  
</P>
<P>
	Rojas started the season in Los Angeles, where he allowed seven  
runs in five innings before being traded to Detroit. With the 
Tigers, Rojas was even worse, giving up 16 runs in 6 1-3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Since leaving Montreal to sign a free agent contract with the  
Chicago Cubs following the 1996 season, Rojas is 5-7 with 17 saves 
and a 6.17 ERA for the Cubs, Dodgers, Mets and Tigers. 
</P>
<P>
	From 1990 to 1996 in Montreal, he was 29-23 with 109 saves and a  
3.04 ERA. 
</P>
