<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990517.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-17 22:21:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> CVS Buys Online Pharmacy Soma.com </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Could any of the handful of tiny online  
pharmacies do to drug sales the way Amazon.com did to bookselling? 
</P>
<P>
	CVS Corp., the nation's second largest pharmacy chain, isn't  
taking any chances. 
</P>
<P>
	CVS is buying online drug retailer Soma.com for $30 million.  
That's a drop in the bucket for CVS, which last year made nearly 
$400 million profit on $15.2 billion in sales. 
</P>
<P>
	The relatively low selling price raised doubts the future of  
independent online pharmacies, which also includes Drugstore.com 
and PlanetRX Inc. and RX.com, an analyst said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Either CVS negotiated the most amazing deal ... or stand alone  
online pharmacies don't have the value some first thought,'' said 
Mark Husson, a Merrill Lynch analyst. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal, announced Monday, accelerates CVS' fledgling effort to  
sell drugs over the Internet, a concept that some experts predict 
could take off the way Amazon.com has transformed the bookselling 
business. 
</P>
<P>
	Soma.com gives CVS a major presence on the Internet, a warehouse  
distribution system, and the ability to sell drugs even in areas of 
the country where CVS has no stores. CVS has 4,122 stores, more 
than any other pharmacy chain. Most of its stores are east of the 
Mississippi River. 
</P>
<P>
	Woonsocket R.I.-based CVS provides Soma.com with instant name  
recognition and contracts to sell to members of many major health 
insurers. CVS officials say they have not decided whether to retain 
the Soma.com web site, its CVS.com or use another name. 
</P>
<P>
	Seattle-based Soma.com in January became the first Internet  
company to launch an online pharmacy. But analysts say the company 
was hampered by few health insurance contracts, which greatly 
limited the number of potential customers that could shop on its 
Web site. Additionally, because Soma.com could only fill orders for 
overnight delivery, it was of little use for patients who wanted 
their medications immediately after leaving the hospital or 
doctor's office. 
</P>
<P>
	Pending federal antitrust approval, the deal should be completed  
in June, company officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	``CVS plus Soma.com is a powerful combination,'' Husson said.  
</P>
<P>
	But he said the low price shows that online pharmacies have some  
inherent problems. He added the CVS-Soma.com deal could spur 
similar mergers. 
</P>
<P>
	``The .coms were supposed to be a major threat to bricks and  
mortar pharmacies, but today we've seen one decide to sell itself 
for a surprisingly small amount of money,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Neither CVS nor privately-held Soma.com would disclose how many  
customers Soma.com has. 
</P>
<P>
	In April, CVS announced plans to enhance its Internet site. The  
company quickly figured buying Soma.com would give it a head start 
over its traditional rivals, said Tom Ryan, CVS chairman and chief 
executive officer. Walgreen, the nation's largest pharmacy chain by 
revenue, and No. 3 Rite Aid are also improving their Internet 
sites. 
</P>
<P>
	CVS has no plans to actively persuade its customers to buy drug  
online, but will make sure consumer are aware they have the option, 
Ryan said. 


</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
