<HEADLINE> Compaq To Cut 900 Jobs in N.H. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALEM, N.H. (AP) -- Compaq Computer Corp. will shut down its  
Salem plant in six to nine months and move many of the plant's 900 
jobs to California and Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	The company is consolidating North American manufacturing to  
plants in Fremont, Calif., and Houston, Compaq said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Salem plant makes Alpha processor-based computer systems.  
</P>
<P>
	Some of the workers at the former Digital Equipment Corp. plant  
will be offered jobs in California and Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a minority of the employees who will be offered the  
opportunity to transfer,'' said Compaq spokesman Alan Hodel. 
</P>
<P>
	About 200 employees who are not involved in manufacturing will  
be transferred to plants in Nashua, Littleton and Maynard, Mass. 
</P>
