<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-17 21:41:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Diamondbacks' Stottlemyre Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Arizona pitcher Todd Stottlemyre left the  
game with tightness in his right shoulder after throwing four 
innings against the San Francisco Giants. 
</P>
<P>
	The Diamondbacks described the move as precautionary and said  
Stottlemyre had no previous problem in his pitching shoulder. He'll 
be evaluated Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Arizona was leading 6-1 when Stottlemyre was lifted. He allowed  
one run and three hits in the abbreviated outing. 
</P>
<P>
	Stottlemyre came out to start the fifth and left the game  
reluctantly after a discussion with manager Buck Showalter and team 
trainers. 
</P>
<P>
	Appearing annoyed, Stottlemyre walked off the field, jawing with  
a fan before retiring to the locker room. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Stottlemyre's first appearance against the Giants since  
he and San Francisco infielder Charlie Hayes were at the center of 
a brawl April 16 in Phoenix. Hayes and Stottlemyre exchanged heated 
words and Hayes charged the pitcher from second base, triggering a 
melee. 
</P>
<P>
	Hayes, who served a four-game suspension for instigating the  
brawl, walked in both plate appearances against Stottlemyre. 
</P>
</TEXT>
