<HEADLINE> Postmaster Accused of Mail Theft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BARRON, Wis. (AP) -- The postmaster in Barron is accused of going  
through the mail and stealing a blood sample taken after he was 
arrested on suspicion of drunken driving. 
</P>
<P>
	Rhon A. Boese, 41, was charged with drunken driving and theft  
and could get nearly two years in jail and $12,000 in fines. 
</P>
<P>
	Boese was arrested on suspicion of drunken driving on March 6. A  
blood sample was drawn at the hospital, and a sheriff's deputy 
dropped it in the mail, but the state laboratory reported that it 
never arrived. 
</P>
<P>
	A postal worker told authorities Boese had come into the post  
office the morning after his arrest and asked a fellow employee to 
``see what he could do.'' The employee didn't want to get involved, 
authorities say. 
</P>
<P>
	When asked about the missing sample and the possibility he stole  
it, Boese told investigators: ``I would never risk my job and throw 
away everything I have worked so hard for. That would be stupid.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
