<HEADLINE> Japan's Average Wage Fell in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Average monthly wages for Japanese workers fell  
last year for the first time since the government started keeping 
track of the numbers in 1970, the Labor Ministry said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The average monthly wage for workers at companies with at least  
30 employees fell 1.6 percent in the fiscal year ending March 31, 
compared to a year earlier, to 409,234 yen ($3,327), the ministry 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Average monthly overtime pay sank 7.3 percent to 23,804 yen  
($194), reflecting a drop in overtime work as a result of the 
prolonged economic slump in Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
