<HEADLINE> Clintons May Visit Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Hillary and Chelsea Clinton may visit Israel  
and Jordan soon, making up for a trip that was postponed because of 
Israel's elections and mourning after the death of King Hussein. 
</P>
<P>
	Aides to the first lady are expected to visit both countries in  
the next few days to look at places she might visit, press 
secretary Marsha Berry said. Reports in Israel said the trip was 
planned for the second half of June. 
</P>
<P>
	The visit would be a followup to a 12-day journey through Egypt,  
Morocco and Tunisia in March. That trip was to have included stops 
in Israel and Jordan, partly to balance Arab interests with 
attention to the special U.S.-Israeli relationship. But Mrs. 
Clinton said then that diplomatic sensitivities to the Israeli 
elections and mourning over Hussein forced postponement of both 
visits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
