<HEADLINE> Devil Rays Activate Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Tampa Bay's Miguel Cairo, sidelined  
since April 23 with a strained right hamstring, was activated from 
the 15-day disabled list on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The second baseman was hitting .295 and had appeared in a  
franchise-best 53 consecutive games being injured in the fourth 
inning of a game against the Seattle Mariners. He played three 
games for Double-A Orlando in a rehab assignment before returning 
to the Devil Rays for Monday night's game at Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	To make room for Cairo, infielder Bobby Smith was optioned to  
Triple-A Durham. He was batting .151 with two homers and four RBIs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
