<HEADLINE> Teen Falls to Death on Prom Night </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AVALON, Calif. (AP) -- A high school student celebrating prom  
night fell from the rooftop of a hotel early Sunday and died 
several hours later with massive head injuries, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	David Ramirez Jr., 18, and a fellow Avalon High School student  
were walking down the sloped roof to return to the inside of the 
Glenmore Hotel on Catalina Island about 2:30 a.m. when Ramirez 
slipped and fell four stories, said Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Deputy Bruce Thomas. 
</P>
<P>
	The students had gone to the roof to smoke, apparently accessing  
the roof by hoisting themselves up from a balcony, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	It was not immediately clear if alcohol was involved in the  
teen-ager's death. Toxicology tests were planned. 
</P>
