<HEADLINE> Expansion Team Ticket Sales Strong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PAUL (AP) -- The Minnesota Wild surpassed 12,000 season  
ticket deposits 17 months before the NHL expansion team begins 
play. 
</P>
<P>
	The club must secure 12,000 paid-in-full season ticket deposits  
by next March 31, according to NHL expansion guidelines. The team 
said Monday it reached that number. 
</P>
<P>
	Fans are sending $100 down payments on season tickets, the cost  
of which will be determined later this year. Single-game ticket 
prices are expected to range from $15 in the balconies to $100 
rinkside. 
</P>
