<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Knee Lands Indians' Alomar on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Bone spurs, not his lack of cartilage, is  
what's causing the pain in Indians catcher Sandy Alomar's knee. 
</P>
<P>
	Alomar, who underwent offseason surgery on his left knee, was  
placed on the 15-day disabled list Monday. He's hoping a cortisone 
injection will get rid of the pain, but if the knee isn't better by 
Tuesday, he said he'll consider having surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	The six-time All-Star thinks he'd probably miss at least a month  
if surgery is needed. 
</P>
<P>
	``I have two bone chips that either moved and it's irritating  
the capsule or the capsule has swelled up a bit,'' he said before 
Cleveland's game in Chicago. ``I don't want this to be a lingering 
problem. It's not going to help me or the help the club.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Alomar had missed five games since May 10 with soreness in the  
knee before the club decided to put him on the DL, retroactive to 
May 11. Chris Turner was recalled from Triple-A Buffalo to fill 
Alomar's spot and will back up Einar Diaz. 
</P>
<P>
	``Any time you lose an All-Star, it's disappointing,'' manager  
Mike Hargrove said. ``We're very fortunate we've got a capable 
back-up. And he hasn't died, so he will be back.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Because he has such little cartilage in his left knee following  
several operations, Alomar has been getting injections of hylagen, 
a lubricant that eases soreness caused by bone rubbing on bone. 
</P>
<P>
	The procedure is relatively new, and after getting a shot last  
week, Alomar thought he would be able to return for the three-game 
weekend series in Detroit. But the soreness persisted, and doctors 
finally realized it was the bone chips causing the problems, not 
the lack of cartilage. 
</P>
<P>
	``My knee is fine. The shots have done what they're supposed to  
do,'' Alomar said. ``It was that I aggravated one of the bone 
chips.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The cortisone shot seems to have helped some, Alomar said. He  
hopes it will reduce the swelling in the capsule enough so the bone 
chip will stop rubbing against it. 
</P>
<P>
	``If it doesn't do that, you'll see me on the table getting  
surgery,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Alomar said he's had the chips for at least three years, but  
they've never bothered him. Doctors decided not to remove them when 
he had surgery because they weren't causing problems and they 
didn't want to disturb the structure of the knee. 
</P>
<P>
	Nagging injuries limited Alomar to 117 games last year.  
</P>
<P>
	Alomar is batting .317 with three homers and 16 RBIs in 22 games  
this season. Earlier this year, he missed six games with lower back 
spasms. 
</P>
<P>
	Turner was batting .319 with two homers and five RBIs in 20  
games for Buffalo. 
</P>
<P>
	The Indians also transferred outfielder Mark Whiten from the  
15-day DL to the 60-day. Whiten has a broken right foot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
