<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-17 15:31:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Indy 500 Crash Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Crashes during practice for the May 30  
Indianapolis 500, with date, driver, car number, chassis-engine and 
description of the crash (r-rookie): 
</P>
<P>
	1, May 16 -- Billy Boat, No. 11, Dallara-Aurora, made a half-spin  
coming out of the first turn, hit the outside wall, made another 
half-spin and stopped at the start of the second turn. The car had 
heavy damage to the left side and rear. Boat was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
	2, May 17 -- r-Mike Borkowski, No. 18, G Force-Aurora, made a  
half-spin coming out of the second turn, hit the wall with the left 
side and slid 1,400 feet along the wall. The car had left-side 
damage. Borkowski was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
	3, May 17 -- Scott Harrington, No. 66T, Dallara-Aurora, struck  
the outside wall twice coming out of the third turn, made 2 1/2 spins 
and stopped in the middle of the fourth turn. The car had extensive 
damage to the right side. Harrington was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
	4, May 17 -- Billy Boat, No. 11, Dallara-Aurora, went into the  
wall coming out of the third turn and came to rest in the north 
chute between turns three and four. The car had right-side damage. 
Boat was not injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
