<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Seeger Celebrates 80th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CROTON-ON-HUDSON, N.Y. (AP) -- Pete Seeger celebrated his 80th  
birthday by doing what he does best: strumming the banjo and 
leading a singalong. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm very honored to be here,'' he said Sunday at the annual  
Riverlovers Shadfest in Croton Point Park on the Hudson River. 
``It's one of my favorite spots.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The event marks the annual shad run, when the oily little fish  
detours from the ocean to spawn in the Hudson. This year's 
observance also honored Seeger, the folk-singing legend whose 
birthday was May 3. He has long been associated with Clearwater, 
the clean-river organization. 
</P>
<P>
	In jeans and a red shirt, the white-bearded Seeger played for a  
crowd that sang and swayed to familiar tunes like ``If I Had a 
Hammer.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990517.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-17 20:21:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 49ers Ownership Dispute Cools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Suspended San Francisco 49ers owner Eddie  
DeBartolo and his sister, Denise DeBartolo York, agreed Monday to a 
one-month truce in their feud over the team. 
</P>
<P>
	York filed a lawsuit last month seeking to oust DeBartolo from  
any management role with the 49ers and demanding he repay $94 
million to the Edward J. DeBartolo Corp. 
</P>
<P>
	DeBartolo filed a countersuit asking a judge to rescind his sale  
of the team to the family-run corporation. He asked for more than 
$650 million in damages from his sister. 
</P>
<P>
	In Akron, Ohio, on Monday, U.S. District Judge Daniel Polster  
asked both sides to suspend litigation against each other for one 
month and begin settlement talks, Polster told the San Francisco 
Examiner. 
</P>
<P>
	``Both sides said they would give it their best effort,'' York  
spokesman Sam Singer told The Associated Press. 
</P>
<P>
	The judge asked the siblings to return to court on June 15 and  
advised them not to talk to reporters about the progress of the 
talks. 
</P>
<P>
	``He asked them to keep their comments private so that the  
process could continue confidentially in order to try and reach a 
settlement,'' Singer said. 
</P>
<P>
	DeBartolo spokesman Rick Rice did not immediately return a  
message left Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The NFL has suspended DeBartolo through February 2000 and fined  
him $1 million for his role in a Louisiana gambling and bribery 
case. DeBartolo pleaded guilty to failing to report a felony. 
</P>
<P>
	In April, York sued her brother in San Francisco, charging him  
with reneging on a $94 million debt to the family company and 
cutting an improper side deal with a prospective developer on a 
stadium-shopping mall project. 
</P>
<P>
	DeBartolo responded with a lawsuit in Ohio, accusing her of  
breach of contract. Polster presides over that suit, but the talks 
could include a settlement of the San Francisco suit, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	In San Francisco, the feud has stalled the stadium project  
approved by voters in June 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
