<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Prices Open Lower / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened lower today. The Dow  
Jones Industrial Average is down 21 points. Losers on the New York 
Stock Exchange hold a 9-5 lead over gainers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is down 11 points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is down three points. 
</P>
<P>
	Despite some weakness in early trading, Wall Street is getting a  
little bit of help from the bond market this morning. 
</P>
<P>
	Bond prices are edging higher, sending yields lower. And that's  
taking some of the pressure off the equities market. 
</P>
<P>
	Stocks were sharply lower on Friday, as the bond market reacted  
negatively to the latest inflation news. 
</P>
<P>
	Overseas stock markets have been lower across the board today.  
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street does have plenty in the way of mergers and  
acquisitions news today, with deals in the telecom, aviation and 
farm-equipment industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
